<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1323,558,1345]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,408,558,584]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Description</emphasis>
. Head: Clypeus with prominent lateral lobes (
<figureCitation box="[1008,1103,559,585]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 22. 19 – 21" captionStartId="15.[264,382,1139,1163]" captionTargetBox="[269,1319,329,1113]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[264,1323,326,1115]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 22. 19 – 21. Head (dorsal view). 19, Aspidoglossa subangulata; 20, Semiardistomis viridis; 21, Ardistomis schaumii. 22, Extremity of body (lateral view) of Ardistomis schaumii. Scale bar = 0.2 mm (Figs 20 – 22), 0.5 mm (Fig. 19)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173808/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[1071,1103,559,585]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
). Antennomere 
<number box="[1308,1322,559,585]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
subequal in length to antennomere 
<number box="[682,699,599,625]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.0">3</number>
. Prothorax: Proepisternum without diagonal band of sculpture. Elytra: Striae punctate, punctures without setae. Lateral margin not prolonged beside basal extremity (
<figureCitation box="[541,628,679,705]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 26. 23 – 24" captionStartId="16.[264,382,1139,1163]" captionTargetBox="[267,1323,326,1113]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[264,1323,326,1113]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 26. 23 – 24. Protarsomeres (ventral view). 23, Aspidoglossa subangulata ɗ; 24, Aspidoglossa subangulata Ψ. 25 – 26. Humeral region (dorsal view). 25, Aspidoglossa subangulata; 26, Semiardistomis viridis. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173809/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[595,628,679,705]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
). Metathorax (underside): Metasternum without setae, with row of punctures along metepisternal suture (except in 
<taxonomicName box="[936,1078,719,744]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Aspidoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ogloblini">
<emphasis box="[936,1078,719,744]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">A. ogloblini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Abdomen: Visible abdominal sterna 
<number box="[474,518,759,785]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3–6</number>
without accessory setae. Suture between visible abdominal sterna 
<number box="[1308,1323,759,785]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
and 
<number box="[317,331,799,825]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.0">3</number>
distinct at middle. Legs: Ventral surface of protibia with one denticule (bearing a seta) in 
<taxonomicName box="[361,492,839,864]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Aspidoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cribrata">
<emphasis box="[361,492,839,864]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">A. cribrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[553,693,839,864]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Aspidoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ogloblini">
<emphasis box="[553,693,839,864]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">A. ogloblini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with longitudinal row of denticules (each bearing a seta at its base) in other species studied (
<figureCitation box="[740,828,879,905]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 30. 27" captionStartId="17.[264,383,1120,1144]" captionTargetBox="[264,1318,314,1105]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[264,1323,314,1106]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 30. 27, Prosternum of Ardistomis schaumii. 28 – 30. Protibia (ventral view). 28, Aspidoglossa subangulata; 29, Semiardistomis viridis; 30, Ardistomis schaumii. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173810/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[795,828,879,905]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
